@startuml flight_plan_incremental_persistence

title JetPass — Persistencia incremental (PATCH por paso)

actor Piloto as Pilot
participant "App" as App
participant "API" as API
participant "Service" as Service
database "PostgreSQL\n(source of truth)" as DB

note over Pilot, DB
  El backend es la única fuente de verdad:
  cada paso hace PATCH sobre el borrador,
  no se acumula nada en el dispositivo.
end note

== Inicia el plan ==
Pilot -> App : Completa Casilla 7
App -> API : POST /flight-plans { departure, destination, ... }
API -> DB : INSERT (status='draft')
API --> App : 201 { plan_id }

== PATCH de un solo paso (Casilla 8) ==
Pilot -> App : Elige flight_rules=V, flight_type=G
App -> API : PATCH /flight-plans/{plan_id}\n{ "flight_rules": "V",\n  "flight_type": "G" }
API -> Service : update_draft(payload)
Service -> Service : model_dump(\n  exclude_unset=True)
note right of Service
  Solo persiste los campos
  presentes en el body.
end note
Service -> DB : UPDATE flight_plans\nSET flight_rules='V',\n    flight_type='G'\nWHERE id=plan_id
API --> App : 200 { plan actualizado }

== Reapertura tras corte ==
Pilot -> App : Reabre la app
App -> API : GET /flight-plans/{plan_id}
API -> DB : SELECT * WHERE id=plan_id
API --> App : 200 { plan con lo ya guardado }
note over App : Reconstruye el wizard\nen el mismo paso.

@enduml
